# BLIND Defensive Use Addendum

BLIND is a defensive user-mode EDR-sensor runtime for owned-process telemetry,
hook diagnostics, launch-gate validation, SDK host integration, and secure
systems analysis. It is provided for authorized security research, detection
engineering, lab validation, defensive education, regression testing, and
endpoint-sensor development.

For this distribution, "permitted purpose" means a noncommercial purpose that is
also authorized, defensive, and lawful. The permissions in the PolyForm
Noncommercial License below apply only to those permitted purposes.

You may not use, modify, distribute, operate, or publish derivative works of this
software for any of the following purposes:

- unauthorized access to, monitoring of, control of, persistence on, or
  interference with any third-party system, account, network, device, service,
  or data;
- offensive cyber operations, intrusion campaigns, cyber command and control,
  credential theft, data theft, extortion, destructive activity, or deployment
  against systems without explicit authorization;
- developing, testing, validating, or improving malware, evasion, stealth,
  persistence, anti-analysis, bypass, or post-exploitation capabilities for
  unauthorized activity;
- operating the software as a remote access tool, implant, loader, dropper,
  botnet component, exploit delivery mechanism, or unauthorized surveillance
  system;
- adding arbitrary-PID attach, persistence, stealth loading, uncontrolled remote
  deployment, hidden-thread filtering, module unlinking, or kernel-driver
  control paths without formal Titan authorization;
- removing, weakening, or misrepresenting this addendum, required notices,
  safety warnings, DSGL/export-control notice, or defensive-use limitations when
  sharing the software or derivative works.

You are responsible for complying with all applicable laws, sanctions,
export-control requirements, government procurement rules, organizational
policies, and authorization boundaries before using, modifying, distributing,
exporting, supplying, or publishing this software or related technical
